 MOSCOW, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Chief of staff of the Russian Northern Fleet Mikhail Motsak on Monday officially confirmed the death of the 118 crew aboard the Kursk nuclear submarine that went down to the bottom of the Barents Sea on August 12. 

 Mostsak told the state RTR television that all the compartments of the submarine are filled with water and that none of the crewmembers survived. 

